What drove her to do that?
I questioned one of the highest generals about what he knew about communism back then. "I had no idea then, just like I do now," he replied. "I even doubt that Mao himself knew what that was." For him, who had survived extreme poverty and oppression, communism was a beautiful dream that kept him alive, the hope for a fair and progressive society.
Nobody perhaps – or could know – how much suffering was still to come, how big the sacrifice and how enormous the difference between dream and reality would be.
